Abstract
This project builds a recipe intelligence platform that predicts user ratings from recipe content and recommends dishes through a conversational AI assistant. Large-scale data processing is handled in PySpark, with regression and clustering models (Scikit-learn, XGBoost) built in Python to predict ratings and group recipes into cuisine archetypes; cleaned data is stored in SQL and visualized through Tableau dashboards. The Generative AI layer uses an agentic, LangChain-orchestrated pipeline — a retrieval agent embeds recipe text into a FAISS vector store, and a reasoning agent (powered by an LLM) answers queries and recommends dishes using Retrieval-Augmented Generation, keeping every response grounded in real recipe data — deployed as an interactive Streamlit application.
